---
description: Laravel Module Maker conventions (generated by jw:ai:init v{{ packageVersion }})
alwaysApply: true
---

Before generating any code in this repository, read `.ai/summary.md`.
For detail load `.ai/ai-rules.md`, `.ai/conventions.md`, and `.ai/generators.md`,
or query the `module-maker` MCP server (`get_guidelines`, `list_modules`,
`module_structure`, `generator_info`, `run_generator`).

Hard rules:
- Never hand-create files under the modules directory — use the `jw:*` artisan generators.
- Features live in isolated modules; app-level Http/Models/routes are off-limits for module features.
- Business logic in module Services; validation in FormRequests; API output via Resources.
- Maintain `$fillable` on every model; tables plural snake_case; models singular StudlyCase; UUID keys.
- Never modify vendor/; project-wide behavior goes in the App\Modules\Core bridge classes.

Regenerate this file with `php artisan jw:ai:init --refresh` — do not edit by hand.
